You can also view the text behind the image,
save the image as a PDF or JPEG to file

00:11:11.560 --> 00:11:19.260 position:58%
or clip a detail from the image which
I'll go over in a couple minutes.

00:11:19.260 --> 00:11:24.000 position:56%
So, the Zoom feature allows you to
focus on the keywords that you found

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:29.800 position:66%
or read smaller text in a particular page.

00:11:29.800 --> 00:11:37.100 position:73%
What you can see on this image here, hopefully,
is that the Zoom feature is outlined in red

00:11:37.100 --> 00:11:41.760
in the box on the top right corner.

00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:50.270 position:56%
So if you -- I've used this as an
example, where, if you want to, say,

00:11:50.270 --> 00:11:55.050 position:72%
clip this image as a detail, what you would
do would be to go to that clipping tool that's

00:11:55.050 --> 00:12:04.410 position:72%
on the right of the toolbox and it will allow
you to save a JPEG of that image for your use.

00:12:04.410 --> 00:12:08.960
Which you can repurpose into
a, you know, presentations,

00:12:08.960 --> 00:12:13.720
online presentations, you
can print out, save to file.

00:12:13.720 --> 00:12:20.290 position:61%
As I mentioned, all the material that's
available here is freely available.

00:12:20.290 --> 00:12:25.100 position:56%
There's no known rights restrictions
associated with this material.

00:12:25.100 --> 00:12:28.160 position:58%
It should all be in the public domain
as far as the library is aware.

00:12:28.160 --> 00:12:33.890 position:58%
So your stud -- you and your students
can feel free to use this material

00:12:33.890 --> 00:12:36.320 position:64%
for your research and your presentations.

00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:42.080
One thing people find particularly
useful is that permanent link.

00:12:42.080 --> 00:12:45.180
Which you see -- I've, kind
of, tried to highlight here,

00:12:45.180 --> 00:12:48.230
that's the same link that's
at the bottom of every page.

